Top Dumbbell Calf-Focused Exercises
1. Dumbbell Standing Calf Raise

Hold dumbbells at your sides.

Rise onto balls of your feet, slow on the way down.

Works mainly gastrocnemius.

2. Dumbbell Elevated Standing Calf Raise

Stand with the balls of your feet on a step/plate.

Dumbbells in hands.

Allows a deeper stretch, increasing activation.

3. Dumbbell Single-Leg Calf Raise

Use one dumbbell in the same-side hand for balance.

Much harder and helps correct imbalances.

Can be done elevated or flat.

4. Dumbbell Donkey Calf Raise (Bent-Over)

Hold a dumbbell between legs while bent forward, hands supported on a bench or rack.

Slight forward lean shifts bias toward the gastrocnemius.

5. Dumbbell Seated Calf Raise

Sit on a bench.

Place dumbbells on your knees/thighs.

Rise onto balls of feet.

Best for targeting the soleus muscle.

6. Dumbbell Tip-Toe Farmer Walk

Hold heavy dumbbells.

Walk forward while staying on your tip-toes.

Burns both calf muscles and improves endurance.

7. Dumbbell Calf Raise with Toes Turned Out

Heels together, toes outward (â€œVâ€ stance).

Emphasizes inner gastrocnemius.

8. Dumbbell Calf Raise with Toes Turned In

Toes inward, heels apart.

Emphasizes outer gastrocnemius.

